H.1 verify (2026-05-14):

Scope: row-level locking on the cron-kicker's poll sweep so two
       concurrent invocations (an EventBridge tick + a future H.4
       self-invocation, or any other parallel sweep) cannot
       double-claim the same composio_poll_state row. Adds a
       tentative-lease bump on next_poll_at so claimed rows stay
       invisible to other sweeps even after the row lock releases
       on commit.

Files landed:
  worker/cron-kicker/handler.ts        (MODIFIED — new
    TENTATIVE_LEASE_SECONDS const (default 300s, env-overridable
    via POLL_TENTATIVE_LEASE_SECONDS). The pollComposioTriggers
    SELECT replaced by an `await sql.begin(async (tx) => { ... })`
    block containing:
      1. SELECT … FROM composio_poll_state WHERE next_poll_at <=
         now() AND paused_at IS NULL ORDER BY next_poll_at ASC
         LIMIT $POLL_BATCH_SIZE FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED
      2. UPDATE composio_poll_state SET next_poll_at = now() +
         (lease_secs * interval '1 second') WHERE id = ANY(claimed
         ids ::uuid[])
    The transaction returns the claimed rows; per-row processing
    after the txn is unchanged.)
  worker/cron-kicker/handler.test.ts   (MODIFIED — sqlTagFn now
    exposes .begin(cb) which forwards to the same tag fn so all
    statements inside `sql.begin` still hit sqlCalls. +2 new H.1
    tests.)

Static checks:
  ✓ pnpm -F @basics/worker exec vitest run cron-kicker/handler
